2026-04-20T05:33:08.474Z JOY-00F7-91 comment.added "[x] rename_project_delegations helper in auth::delegation with unit tests (move, missing-source no-op, target-exists error, same-id no-op).\n[x] project_id_of helper in auth::session to compute project_id from an in-memory Project without re-reading yaml.\n[x] set_value call-site in project.rs captures old project_id before mutation, migrates delegation dir atomically after acronym change, before writing project.yaml. Rename failure aborts the acronym change.\n[x] Added CLI note: existing sessions and delegation tokens reference the old acronym and are invalidated; user should re-auth and reissue.\n[x] Three bats integration tests: migrate directory, refuse on target collision, no-op when no delegation dir exists.\n[x] Full cargo test and bats auth.bats suites pass.\n\nNote: Session files are also project_id-scoped (SHA-256 hash) and become stale across an acronym rename. Not migrated here because sessions are 24h ephemerals and re-auth is cheap; user is warned in the CLI output. Delegation keys are SSH-key-class secrets and genuinely needed migration." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
